Those who like to walk on the Wild West side will no doubt be intrigued to learn that one of Buffalo Bill’s favorite guns is going up for auction, almost 100 years after his death.

The legendary showman - real name William Cody - bought the six-shooter revolver in 1883, the same year he launched his circus-style travelling show, which famously featured Sioux Indian Sitting Bull.

He was one of the most iconic characters from the American Old West era and was a contemporary of Calamity Jane and Wild Bill Hickok.

