Although unremarkable to look at, the gun became one of Cody's favourite firearms and was among the few he still owned at the time of his death aged 70 in 1917 from kidney failure.

Cody, who earned his nickname hunting buffalo as a young man, was known for his generosity and although he owned many guns during his successful career he gave most of them away.

He bought the gun at Hartley and Graham in New York while on extended stay with his theatre troupe.

